cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE. 

The paper introduces normal forms for logic programs under stable/answer set semantics, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence and logic. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the study of program properties and consistency, which are topics related to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also introduces a novel graph-like representation of programs, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
